cs.LG, cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.IT 

This paper is about game-theoretic machine learning, which involves learning optimal mechanisms for self-interested agents in internet applications. This topic is closely related to machine learning (cs.LG), game theory (cs.GT), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), data structures (cs.DS), and information theory (cs.IT). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely.
